Philippi is among areas where there have been violent demonstrations over the past few months - mostly due to a lack of housing and land. CAPE TOWN - Law enforcement officials are monitoring a section of Philippi where residents have marked out plots of land. Philippi is among areas where there have been violent demonstrations over the past few months - mostly due to a lack of housing and land. Law enforcement spokesperson Wayne Dyason said: “A group of people is marking out plots in Samora Machel, law enforcement is monitoring the area and everything is currently quiet.”